photo dump from a couple weeks ago in San Diego and Nashville 🌊💕🤠

2022 taught me how to appreciate the moment as it doesn’t last forever. 

i couldn’t have done any of this without you - whether you’re one of my best friends, a client i’ve gotten to spend a few hours with, one of my long distant friendships, or simply follow along and support my art virtually. 

the fact that there are people all around the U.S. and in other countries/continents with tattoos i’ve given them is mindboggling. the fact that i’ve gotten to meet people all around the world - some now lifelong friends and some who i’ve shared an unforgettable moment with. the fact that this all happened in the past 365 days is not something i think i’ll ever fully comprehend.

there is no way to capture it all in a social media post, so here’s just a few highlights of this year and some of the people who made it special.

xx marissa monroe

p.s. im also gonna post the video as a reel bc i couldn’t figure out how to add music and crop it correctly here, so go watch it there instead plz
